g.text: Migrants pay $50-$100 to travel by rafts and other small boats to cross the river. The average migrant has spent $1,064 by the time they have gotten to the Mexico border.
Migrants pay $50-$100 to travel by rafts and other small boats to cross the river. The average migrant has spent $1,064 by the time they have gotten to the Mexico border.

Non-profits such as Casa del Migrante struggle to provide food, water, and shelter to the migrants passing through and preference housing families for their safety. The typicallycan house 100 hundred migrants but have housed 500 when caravans pass through.

Mexico is often put in the position of immigration enforcer.On January 2020 there was an altercation as they blocked an estimated 2,500 migrants on the bridge spanning theSuchiate River as they attempted to push their way through.
